Enjoy banking at your fingertips – anytime,
anywhere. Now you can do your personal
banking securely from your mobile. Kina Personal
Online Banking app lets you manage your
existing Kina Bank transactional and savings
accounts. 

You’ll be happy to know you’ll be able to do
almost all the things you’d normally do at a
Kina Bank branch – like transfer funds, make
payments, view your accounts, check balances,
download online statements and much more. 

To start using Kina Personal Online Banking, you’ll
need to be an existing Kina Bank customer. Then,
simply visit Kina Personal Online Banking on the
Kina Bank website and create an account. Fill
out the online form, including your existing Kina
Bank account details, and soon you’ll be banking
securely and quickly anytime or anywhere you
choose!

It’s free to use Kina Personal Online Banking, but
the accounts you manage there will have their
normal associated fees.

StarTrip is the ride-hailing app built for the Pacific, giving riders safe, reliable, and comfortable trips at the tap of a button. Whether you’re commuting to work, heading out with friends, or simply need a quick ride across town, StarTrip makes every journey simple and stress-free.

With a sleek, easy-to-use design and a growing community of trusted drivers, StarTrip is more than just transportation—it’s your companion for moving with confidence.



Why Choose StarTrip?
        •        Fast & Reliable
Book a ride in seconds and connect with nearby drivers who are ready to get you where you need to go.
        •        Safe & Secure
Every ride is tracked in real time, and every driver is verified, giving you peace of mind from pickup to drop-off.
        •        Comfortable & Convenient
Enjoy rides in clean vehicles, matched with drivers who care about delivering a great experience.
        •        Transparent Pricing
Know your fare upfront—no hidden fees, no surprises. Just fair, simple pricing every time.
        •        Designed for the Pacific
StarTrip understands the unique needs of Pacific communities. Our platform is built to make everyday travel accessible, affordable, and tailored to local lifestyles.


Features You’ll Love
        •        One-Tap Booking – Request a ride instantly and get matched with a nearby driver.
        •        Live Tracking – Watch your driver’s arrival in real time, so you’re never left waiting.
        •        Upfront Fares – See exactly what you’ll pay before confirming your ride.
        •        Driver Profiles – View driver details and ratings for extra confidence.
        •        In-App Support – Access help directly within the app whenever you need it.
        •        Cashless & Simple – Pay securely and track your trip history with ease.



Your Everyday Travel Partner

StarTrip is designed to make every trip easier, whether it’s a quick ride around the neighborhood or a longer journey across the city. Our mission is to provide riders with confidence and convenience, supported by technology that puts you first.

We go beyond just connecting riders and drivers—we’re building a transportation ecosystem that strengthens communities, creates opportunities, and modernizes travel across the Pacific.



Built on Trust & Community

Every StarTrip ride is more than just a trip. It’s about trust, respect, and a shared commitment to better mobility. Our drivers are part of your community, and every ride helps support local opportunities and growth.

When you ride with StarTrip, you’re not just choosing a service—you’re joining a movement that believes in safety, fairness, and reliability for all.



Join the Movement

Getting started is simple. Download the StarTrip app, sign up in minutes, and book your first ride. Wherever you need to go, StarTrip is ready to take you there—fast, safe, and with confidence.

It’s your city. Your ride. Your confidence.
Choose StarTrip today and experience the future of ride-hailing in the Pacific.

CNCFeedWizard is a handy calculator app made for machinists, CNC programmers, and shop owners. It helps you quickly find the right cutting speed and RPM, feed rate, and chip load per tooth for your tools. You can also work out metal removal rate (MRR) to see how fast you’re really cutting. The app includes a tool life prediction calculator using the Taylor equation, so you can plan tool changes better. It can estimate cost per part by combining tooling cost and machine time. You also get tool life per edge or per corner to track insert usage more clearly. For quality control, CNCFeedWizard offers a simple surface finish estimator for turning and milling. It even handles radial chip thinning and spindle power needs, so your feeds and speeds stay safe, efficient, and easy to set.

BoringBarCalc is a handy tool made to help machinists, programmers, and shop owners work faster and smarter. The app brings together many useful machining calculators in one easy place. You can quickly check boring bar overhang, tapping torque, thread milling speeds, and more with simple inputs. It also helps adjust feeds for helical moves, ramps, plunges, and corner cutting. Surface finish, heat input, and other cutting conditions can be understood in seconds. The app even supports planning tasks like tool consumption, reorder timing, and shift capacity. Our goal is to make machining calculations simple, accurate, and easy for everyone. With BoringBarCalc, you save time, avoid mistakes, and improve your machining results.

BoosterPumpHeat helps pump users see how elevation, weather, and water level change suction safety and NPSH margin. The app groups tools for altitude effects, daily pressure swings, tide or river level moves, and floating roof tank drawdown. Users can test strainers, fouling build-up, and suction line heat gain to balance protection, pressure loss, and temperature rise. Hot recirculation mixing, booster heater changes, and inlet velocity checks guide safer adjustments to flow and layout. Clear calculators show best and worst operating windows so cavitation risk becomes easier to spot. Simple inputs, quick graphs, and plain language make pump health checks fast for both operators and engineers. Use BoosterPumpHeat during design reviews, plant changes, or troubleshooting to keep suction conditions inside a safe zone. The app supports smarter, calmer pump decisions before problems appear in the field.

Say more with Threads — Instagram’s text-based conversation app.

Threads is where communities come together to discuss everything from the topics you care about today to what’ll be trending tomorrow. Whatever it is you’re interested in, you can follow and connect directly with your favorite creators and others who love the same things — or build a loyal following of your own to share your ideas, opinions and creativity with the world!

A few things you can do on Threads…

■ Access your Instagram followers
Your Instagram username and verification badge are reserved for you. Automatically follow the same accounts you follow on Instagram in a few taps, and discover new accounts too.

■ Share your point of view
Spin up a new thread to express what's on your mind. This is your space to be yourself, and you control who can reply.

■ Connect with friends and your favorite creators
Jump to the replies to get in on the action and react to commentary, humor and insight from the creators you know and love. Find your community and connect with people who care about whatever it is you’re interested in.

■ Control the conversation
Customize your settings and use controls to manage who can see your content, reply to your threads, or mention you. Accounts you’ve blocked will carry over from Instagram, and we’re enforcing the same Community Guidelines to help ensure everyone interacts safely and authentically. 

■ Find ideas and inspiration
From TV recommendations to career advice, get answers to your questions or learn something new from crowd-sourced conversations, thought leaders and industry experts.

■ Never miss a moment
Stay on top of the latest trends and live events. Whether it’s about new music, movie premieres, sports, games, TV shows, fashion, or the latest product releases, find discussions and receive notifications any time your favorite profiles start a new thread.

■ Leap into the fediverse
Threads is part of the fediverse, a global, open, social network of independent servers operated by third parties around the world. Servers share information with each other to enable people to connect and discover new things across the fediverse.

CutterUsageTracker is a app to keep track of every cutting tool you use on the shop floor. It lets you log tool life with fields like tool code, machine, material, cutting time, parts made, and wear condition so you can see when a cutter really needs to be changed. You can also keep a clean regrind history, noting each regrind number, date, shop, material removed, and current tool size to know how many good runs are left in a tool. Built-in converters help you switch between power, torque, and speed, and between coolant flow units like L/min and gal/min, plus bar and psi for pressure. The app also gives small calculators for engagement time per part, cycle time per part, and best step-over or step-down so you can tune your programs. With all tool and regrind data in one place, you can spot bad cutting conditions, catch root causes, and cut down on sudden tool breaks. CutterUsageTracker helps you use each cutter for the right time, lower tool costs, and keep your machines running more smoothly.

FAQs
Are all features free?
The app is free to download and use, with a mix of free and paid features.

Can I still use my personal WhatsApp?

Introducing Digital Film for iPhone and iPad!
Blackmagic Camera unlocks the power of your iPhone and iPad by adding digital film camera controls and operating systems! Now you can create the same cinematic ‘look’ as Hollywood feature films. You get the same intuitive and user friendly interface as Blackmagic Design’s award winning cameras. So it’s just like using a professional digital film camera! This means you can adjust settings such as frame rate, shutter angle, white balance and ISO all in a single tap. Or record directly to Blackmagic Cloud in industry standard 10-bit Apple ProRes files up to 4K! Recording to Blackmagic Cloud Storage lets you collaborate on DaVinci Resolve projects with editors anywhere in the world, all at the same time!

Get the "Hollywood Look" with Digital Film!
Blackmagic Camera puts the professional features you need for feature film, television and documentaries in your pocket. Now you can create YouTube and TikTok content with a cinematic look, and broadcast quality ENG! Imagine having a run and gun camera on hand to capture breaking news whenever it happens! Or use Blackmagic Camera as a B Cam to capture angles that are difficult to reach with traditional cameras, while still retaining control of important settings. Best of all, recording to Blackmagic Cloud allows you to get your footage to the newsroom or post production studio in minutes.

Interactive Controls for Fast Setup 
Blackmagic Camera has all the controls you need to quickly setup and start shooting!  Everything is interactive, so you can tap any item and instantly change settings without searching through confusing menus! The HUD shows status and record parameters, histogram, focus peaking indicators, levels, frame guides and more. Show or hide the HUD by swiping up or down. You can auto focus by tapping the screen in the area you want to focus. You can shoot in 16:9 or vertical aspect ratios, plus you can shoot 16:9 while holding your phone vertically if you want to shoot unobtrusively.

On Screen Heads Up Display
The heads up display, or HUD, controls have the most important camera controls such as lens selection, frame rate, shutter angle, timecode, ISO, white balance, gain and audio levels. You can adjust settings such as exposure by touching the ISO indicator, or you can change the audio levels simply by touching the audio meters. Everything is interactive, so if you tap any item you can instantaneously change its settings without having to search through complex menus!

Camera Setup Menus
The settings tab unlocks the full power of your phone’s camera, with quick access to advanced settings such as monitoring, audio, camera setup, recording and more! The record tab gives you total control over video resolution and recording format including industry standard Apple ProRes or space efficient H.264 and H.265. Plus, you can set anamorphic de-squeeze and lens correction settings. Professional audio options include AAC and PCM format and VU or PPM audio metering. You can even add external microphones! Or add 3D LUTs to recreate film looks!

Media
The Blackmagic Camera media tab has all the controls you need to browse or scrub clips for quick review, search and sort and view the upload status of your media. Access your media from Blackmagic Camera’s all clips folder by choosing the Media button to see the thumbnails for each clip you have stored. Plus, you can save to the files folder on the phone, send it to Blackmagic Cloud Storage via Blackmagic Cloud or manually choose which clips to upload to a project library. You can even sync media from Blackmagic Camera directly into the DaVinci Resolve project so you’re ready to edit!

Live Sync to Blackmagic Cloud Storage
When shooting with Blackmagic Camera, the video you capture can be instantly uploaded as a proxy file, followed by the camera originals, and saved to Blackmagic Cloud Storage. This means you can start editing quickly using your proxies, speeding up your workflow.

Simple and secure connections, right away
